Sentence: tens of thousands of people are greeting pope john paul ii in croatia. in the port city of dubrovnik , he beatified a nun who dedicated her live to serving the poor. her life to the poor. marija petkovic founded a religious order of nuns in the 1920s that cared for impoverished children in croatia and south america. she is the first croatian woman to be beatified , which is one step before sainthood. the pope also said mass before a crowd of 70,000 people .
